- cut 45mm steaks from pok loin roast (cut skin off to make into crackling)
- dry brine
- cooked internal temp 56°C
- remove from heat at 48°C
- sear at 165°C to allow fat to render, with each surface getting a few turns
- once at 40°C internal, set pan to 130°C and add butter to cool down
- add rosemary and a little bit of thyme and baste a bit
- remove pork to rest
- let herbs infuse for a bit
- remove herbs
- add finely chopped sage, black pepper, and half a can of apple cider
- reduce down a little
- add stock cube (25g our frozen chicken stock)
- add wholegrain mustard and apple sauce to thicken and balance
